CONCEPTUAL INSPIRATIONS (no code reused)
----------------------------------------

1. Andrej Karpathy — "LLM Knowledge Base" concept.
   https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f

   The index-based retrieval approach (read index.md, let the LLM choose
   articles, skip RAG at personal scale) is directly inspired by this
   public gist. No source code was available or consulted.

2. Cole Medin — "claude-memory-compiler".
   https://github.com/coleam00/claude-memory-compiler

   Provided the initial idea of using Claude Code hooks (SessionEnd,
   PreCompact, SessionStart) to automate transcript capture and
   knowledge compilation. The upstream repository has no published
   license; therefore the core scripts in this project (flush.py,
   compile.py, query.py, lint.py, config.py, hook skeletons) were
   written from scratch against the specification in
   docs/architecture.ru.md without consulting upstream source code.
   See docs/clean-room-provenance.md for the audit trail.


